President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. The nominations include Thomas McCaffery as Assistant Secretary of Defense for Health Affairs, Michael Peter Pelletier as Ambassador to Madagascar and the Union of the Comoros, William H. Moser as Ambassador to Kazakhstan, Robert K. Scott as Ambassador to Malawi, Craig Lewis Cloud as Ambassador to Botswana, Michael S. Klecheski as Ambassador to Mongolia, Judith Gail Garber as Ambassador to Cyprus, Donald Armin Blome as Ambassador to Tunisia, and Dennis B. Hankins as Ambassador to Mali. These individuals have extensive experience in various fields and have served in different diplomatic roles across the globe.